# Memory Representation

Program

```java
Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

int age = sc.nextInt();
```

Stack Memory

```
sc
↓

Reference

age
↓

22
```

Heap Memory

```
Scanner Object
```

The reference variable is stored in the stack.

The actual Scanner object is stored in the heap.

---

# Closing Scanner

```java
sc.close();
```

Purpose

- Releases the input resource.
- Considered good programming practice.
- Important in real-world applications.

